Banco Espirito Santo, Santander, Spyker: European Equity Preview

-- B y   J e n n i f e r   A .   J o h n s o n
-- 
2011-03-30T04:00:04Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-29/banco-espirito-santo-santander-spyker-european-equity-preview.html
The following companies’ shares may
have unusual moves in European trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses.  The Stoxx Europe 600 Index advanced 0.1 percent to 276.51.
The Stoxx 50 Index fell less than 0.1 percent to 2,598.51. The
Euro Stoxx 50 Index, a benchmark for nations using the euro,
slumped 0.1 percent to 2,910.93.        Banco Espirito Santo SA (BES)  :  Portugal ’s biggest
publicly traded bank by market value said in a presentation it
sold 1.3 billion euros ($1.8 billion) of loans during the first
quarter. The shares dropped 2.3 percent to 3.02 euros.  Banco Santander SA (SAN)  :  Spain ’s biggest lender
purchased 96 percent of  Poland ’s Bank Zachodni WBK SA for 3.99
billion euros ($5.62 billion) from Allied Irish Banks Plc.
Santander will also buy 50 percent of BZ WBK Asset Management
from Allied Irish for 150 million euros in cash, the Madrid-
based lender said in a statement. Santander shares slipped 1.3
percent to 8.45 euros.       Camaieu (AMA)  : British private equity firm Cinven Ltd.
offered to buy the rest of the designer of women’s clothing. The
shares gained 44 percent to 209.16 euros.  Spyker Cars NV (SPYKR)  : The carmaker’s Saab Automobile
unit is having trouble paying suppliers and production at its
factory in Trollhaettan,  Sweden  was halted,  Dagens Industri 
Reported, citing several people familiar with the plant. The
shares fell 0.8 percent to 4.26 euros.  To contact the reporters on this story:
